1
00:00:09,009 --> 00:00:13,222
The first survivor is…

2
00:00:18,727 --> 00:00:19,937
Noh Seulbi.

3
00:00:20,020 --> 00:00:21,939
NOH SEULBI SURVIVES

4
00:00:24,942 --> 00:00:27,361
Congratulations.

5
00:00:27,945 --> 00:00:29,821
- Whoa.
- Wow.

6
00:00:44,002 --> 00:00:45,420
She's so Gen Z.

7
00:00:45,504 --> 00:00:47,214
She's a real Gen Z.

8
00:00:48,632 --> 00:00:52,928
The late Ko Miyeong
was a sports climber-turned-mountaineer.

9
00:00:53,011 --> 00:00:55,013
On July 11, 2009,

10
00:00:55,097 --> 00:00:58,934
on the way down
after successfully scaling Nanga Parbat

11
00:00:59,017 --> 00:01:00,435
in the Himalayas,

12
00:01:00,519 --> 00:01:03,355
she fell to her death off a cliff.

13
00:01:05,065 --> 00:01:06,275
Mmm…

14
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:09,403
She lost
her footing and died.

15
00:01:09,486 --> 00:01:13,323
I knew it. That's why I said
she fell to her death.

16
00:01:13,991 --> 00:01:15,492
I know. I want to show them.

17
00:01:15,993 --> 00:01:17,369
"Fell while mountain climbing."

18
00:01:17,452 --> 00:01:20,122
FELL WHILE MOUNTAIN CLIMBING

19
00:01:20,205 --> 00:01:23,041
I got everything right.
I wrote it all down.

20
00:01:23,125 --> 00:01:24,668
"She fell off a mountain cliff."

21
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:26,461
I wrote
that she fell from a height.

22
00:01:26,545 --> 00:01:28,589
My neck went stiff,
and I couldn't move it.

23
00:01:28,672 --> 00:01:30,048
She probably broke her neck.

24
00:01:30,132 --> 00:01:31,258
FELL AND INJURED HER HEAD

25
00:01:31,341 --> 00:01:35,554
We unanimously chose Noh Seulbi.

26
00:01:35,637 --> 00:01:38,849
This person passed away in the Himalayas.

27
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:43,687
From your very first words, you completely
captivated us Fate Reapers.

28
00:01:43,770 --> 00:01:45,814
"It's cold and dark."

29
00:01:45,897 --> 00:01:48,233
Then you said she went missing.

30
00:01:48,317 --> 00:01:51,194
You also said she was away from home.

31
00:01:51,278 --> 00:01:53,363
Everything you said made us think

32
00:01:53,447 --> 00:01:55,615
you saw exactly what happened that day.

33
00:01:55,699 --> 00:01:58,076
You got everything accurately.

34
00:01:58,577 --> 00:02:02,372
Now, you asked,
"Are you sure that's when she died?"

35
00:02:02,456 --> 00:02:04,333
Can I ask what you meant by that?

36
00:02:05,542 --> 00:02:07,502
I didn't think that date was right.

37
00:02:08,337 --> 00:02:13,091
Maybe they found her later on,
or that's just when they think she died.

38
00:02:13,842 --> 00:02:15,886
Her body was recovered

39
00:02:15,969 --> 00:02:19,640
after she died, with the help
of other climbers and a helicopter.

40
00:02:19,723 --> 00:02:20,724
Ah…

41
00:02:20,807 --> 00:02:23,060
The date is just an estimate.

42
00:02:23,143 --> 00:02:24,519
Well, that's not when she died.

43
00:02:25,062 --> 00:02:27,147
This is insane.

44
00:02:27,731 --> 00:02:30,108
She's tough. Really tough.

45
00:02:31,818 --> 00:02:35,656
When I first walked
into the hall and looked around,

46
00:02:35,739 --> 00:02:37,366
she had the strongest aura.

47
00:02:38,575 --> 00:02:41,620
She's really something else.

48
00:02:42,204 --> 00:02:43,538
That shaman named Seulbi.

49
00:02:43,622 --> 00:02:46,083
She's spiritually powerful and confident.

50
00:02:46,166 --> 00:02:48,085
She doesn't seem to hesitate.

51
00:02:48,168 --> 00:02:50,337
I thought she was impressive.

52
00:02:51,463 --> 00:02:53,882
She was incredibly accurate.

53
00:02:53,965 --> 00:02:56,635
As a fellow shaman,
I have to give her credit.

54
00:02:56,718 --> 00:03:00,639
Getting all those details right
in such a short time

55
00:03:00,722 --> 00:03:03,767
made me think she was the best there is.

56
00:03:05,102 --> 00:03:09,022
Fate Reader Noh Seulbi survived.

57
00:03:09,106 --> 00:03:10,107
Impressive.

58
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:11,608
She's so cool.

59
00:03:11,692 --> 00:03:15,404
As soon as she got
the first one right, she got up and left.

60
00:03:15,487 --> 00:03:17,114
It was so badass.

61
00:03:17,864 --> 00:03:19,783
I thought her
intuition was so powerful,

62
00:03:19,866 --> 00:03:22,327
and I wanted to be next.

63
00:03:22,953 --> 00:03:24,663
She did get it first,

64
00:03:25,372 --> 00:03:27,124
so I guess she's pretty good.

65
00:03:27,791 --> 00:03:30,752
But it's not over until it's over.

66
00:03:30,836 --> 00:03:32,546
We'll see at the end.

67
00:03:39,261 --> 00:03:41,012
This is hard.

68
00:03:41,096 --> 00:03:42,931
- It's not easy.
- It's hard.

69
00:03:43,473 --> 00:03:45,183
I need to focus harder.

70
00:03:48,687 --> 00:03:50,814
Here is the next question.

71
00:04:00,490 --> 00:04:01,867
It's a man.

72
00:04:06,204 --> 00:04:07,831
KIM CHEOLHONG
DIED ON MARCH 4, 2001

73
00:04:07,914 --> 00:04:09,916
- Another deceased person.
- He's passed away.

74
00:04:10,584 --> 00:04:11,710
Another dead person?

75
00:04:12,627 --> 00:04:14,463
I specialize in reading through spirits,

76
00:04:14,546 --> 00:04:18,175
so I'm confident
when it comes to reading the dead.

77
00:04:19,217 --> 00:04:20,927
Calling and communicating with spirits

78
00:04:21,011 --> 00:04:22,846
is something I'm pretty good at.

79
00:04:22,929 --> 00:04:25,140
I decided to go with what I see and feel.

80
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:28,477
"This is my second chance."

81
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:34,191
The fate for you to read
is the deceased's cause of death.

82
00:04:35,484 --> 00:04:37,110
Please begin your reading now.

83
00:04:38,570 --> 00:04:40,697
SAGE CHEONMYEONG
10-MONTH SHAMAN

84
00:04:40,781 --> 00:04:43,617
I'm sorry to ask this of you,
Granny, Grandpa.

85
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:45,702
The name is Kim Cheolhong.

86
00:04:45,786 --> 00:04:47,954
Kim Cheolhong,
born in the lunar September of 1964.

87
00:04:48,038 --> 00:04:49,456
Show me the cause of death.

88
00:04:50,165 --> 00:04:51,833
He was born
in the Year of the Azure Dragon.

89
00:04:55,754 --> 00:04:58,381
HONG YULJAE
6-YEAR SHAMAN

90
00:04:58,465 --> 00:05:00,175
Show me what happened

91
00:05:00,258 --> 00:05:04,721
at the time of his death,
as if I were there to witness it.

92
00:05:08,016 --> 00:05:09,643
DOEYU
7-YEAR SHAMAN

93
00:05:12,187 --> 00:05:13,688
Someone's whistling.

94
00:05:13,772 --> 00:05:15,023
Whistling?

95
00:05:18,193 --> 00:05:20,779
I don't ring bells.

96
00:05:20,862 --> 00:05:23,198
I whistled to call on my deities

97
00:05:23,281 --> 00:05:27,244
and ask them
to show me his cause of death.

98
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:31,665
I usually keep my shrine very quiet
when I do a reading.

99
00:05:31,748 --> 00:05:35,043
I've never met this many shamans before,

100
00:05:35,126 --> 00:05:38,964
but I've also never heard this many bells
ringing at the same time.

101
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:43,134
Everyone was ringing their bells,
and it was driving me crazy.

102
00:05:46,888 --> 00:05:48,932
I had to focus on my whistling,

103
00:05:49,474 --> 00:05:51,351
so I covered my ears while reading.

104
00:05:53,728 --> 00:05:55,188
I hear whistles from all sides.

105
00:05:55,272 --> 00:05:56,940
Ugh, it's giving me the chills.

106
00:05:58,275 --> 00:05:59,734
Young Master Seo is whistling.

107
00:06:01,361 --> 00:06:02,863
YOUNG MASTER SEO
5-YEAR SHAMAN

108
00:06:02,946 --> 00:06:06,324
Young Master Seo
looks really confident.

109
00:06:06,408 --> 00:06:07,409
Mmm.

110
00:06:07,492 --> 00:06:10,745
I serve my deities in Osan,
Gyeonggi-do.

111
00:06:10,829 --> 00:06:13,164
I go by Young Master Seo
of Cheonshin Shrine.

112
00:06:13,248 --> 00:06:16,543
I used to teach children taekwondo…

113
00:06:18,879 --> 00:06:21,256
…until I was told
I was destined to become a shaman.

114
00:06:21,882 --> 00:06:24,050
So I accepted it
and began serving right away.

115
00:06:24,134 --> 00:06:29,097
Actually, both my mom's and dad's
sides of the family have had shamans

116
00:06:29,180 --> 00:06:31,474
for 3 generations.

117
00:06:31,558 --> 00:06:35,270
So I was confident
about guessing the cause of death.

118
00:06:36,688 --> 00:06:39,858
I got a jigi , and my deities showed me.

119
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:43,695
I'll never disgrace them.

120
00:06:47,741 --> 00:06:51,911
LADY WISH
6-YEAR SHAMAN

121
00:07:00,754 --> 00:07:03,089
I see visions,

122
00:07:03,173 --> 00:07:08,261
so I see how they looked when they died
or what happened to them.

123
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:11,931
A vision is…

124
00:07:13,183 --> 00:07:16,061
When shamans sense something
while trying to read fortune,

125
00:07:16,144 --> 00:07:17,646
some of them see a vision with their eyes.

126
00:07:17,729 --> 00:07:19,481
Some see it with their eyes closed,

127
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:24,235
while others see with their eyes open.

128
00:07:25,612 --> 00:07:27,447
The images play before you like a film.

129
00:07:28,573 --> 00:07:29,699
You see the situation.

130
00:07:35,330 --> 00:07:38,041
-I think shamans are at an advantage here.
-Yes.

131
00:07:38,124 --> 00:07:41,294
- Because they can see what happened.
- Yes.

132
00:07:41,878 --> 00:07:43,505
Someone's yawning.

133
00:07:43,588 --> 00:07:45,632
-That person keeps yawning.
-Oh, no.

134
00:07:45,715 --> 00:07:47,050
Oh, goodness.

135
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:49,678
He looks really tired.

136
00:07:49,761 --> 00:07:50,887
He must be tired.

137
00:07:54,182 --> 00:07:55,183
YOUNG MASTER PLUM BLOSSOM

138
00:07:55,266 --> 00:07:58,061
Whenever I channel
my Granny, Grandpa spirits

139
00:07:58,144 --> 00:08:00,772
and other deities, I yawn a lot.

140
00:08:01,731 --> 00:08:04,609
So, you'll see me yawning a lot.

141
00:08:05,527 --> 00:08:09,447
Sometimes they give me a reading
or even a vision.

142
00:08:09,531 --> 00:08:12,534
My Granny spirit
mostly works with scissors.

143
00:08:16,663 --> 00:08:18,164
And hwatu cards.

144
00:08:18,915 --> 00:08:21,501
She made me pick up the hwatu cards.

145
00:08:22,377 --> 00:08:24,838
I use them to read people's love life,
do a spirit reading,

146
00:08:24,921 --> 00:08:27,966
or read people's finances and life paths.

147
00:08:28,550 --> 00:08:32,846
I looked at the man's photo
and picked out a few cards.

148
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:35,056
All cards had fire on them.

149
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:39,519
Then I asked my Granny spirit
if that was right,

150
00:08:39,602 --> 00:08:42,480
and she said,
"That's for you to find out."

151
00:08:42,564 --> 00:08:44,274
So I started tying the go.

152
00:08:45,608 --> 00:08:48,737
It's called "go,"
but the exact name is "goppae."

153
00:08:50,488 --> 00:08:52,115
We use a black one

154
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:54,784
to call upon the spirits
who died tragically, far from home.

155
00:08:55,410 --> 00:08:58,246
On the fourth day of March in 2001,

156
00:08:58,329 --> 00:09:00,582
he died while doing a good deed.

157
00:09:00,665 --> 00:09:02,792
As I was tying the go into knots,

158
00:09:02,876 --> 00:09:05,754
my Granny spirit said,
"You know what to do, right?"

159
00:09:05,837 --> 00:09:09,049
I said, "I do."
To find out the cause of his death,

160
00:09:09,674 --> 00:09:13,386
I tied the black go into knots
and put the scissors on it.

161
00:09:13,470 --> 00:09:14,929
That's when I felt him.

162
00:09:22,729 --> 00:09:25,273
Just imagine the spirit's lying on the go.

163
00:09:25,356 --> 00:09:27,567
It'd be this big,
lying on top of the cloth.

164
00:09:29,611 --> 00:09:32,781
I got a jigi, and I wanted to jump
into the water in front of me.

165
00:09:32,864 --> 00:09:33,990
It was so hot.

166
00:09:35,033 --> 00:09:37,535
It felt like my skin
was burning from the inside,

167
00:09:37,619 --> 00:09:39,204
so I could do nothing but sit still.

168
00:09:41,539 --> 00:09:43,083
KIM CHEOLHONG
DIED ON MARCH 4, 2001

169
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:45,752
What is his cause of death?

170
00:09:48,797 --> 00:09:50,924
FIREFIGHTER WHO RESPONDED
TO THE HONGJE-DONG ARSON SCENE

171
00:09:51,633 --> 00:09:56,846
ON MARCH 4, 2001, A FIRE BROKE OUT
IN A MULTIPLEX HOUSING UNIT IN HONGJE-DONG

172
00:09:58,223 --> 00:10:00,683
THE CEILING AND WALLS CAVED IN,

173
00:10:00,767 --> 00:10:04,145
BURYING KIM CHEOLHONG
DURING THE RESCUE EFFORTS

174
00:10:04,771 --> 00:10:08,441
THEY TRIED TO RESCUE HIM,

175
00:10:08,525 --> 00:10:12,070
BUT HE DIED UNDER THE RUBBLE

176
00:10:12,654 --> 00:10:15,532
I think I'll have chills
if anyone mentions heat.

177
00:10:15,615 --> 00:10:17,200
- "It's hot."
- "He didn't deserve it."

178
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:19,619
- "He was trapped."
- "He was trapped."

179
00:10:19,702 --> 00:10:23,331
Since the cause of death is clear,
it'll be easier to judge.

180
00:10:24,332 --> 00:10:27,585
I'm wondering
if it was related to a crime.

181
00:10:27,669 --> 00:10:30,338
I think it was an arson case.

182
00:10:30,421 --> 00:10:34,259
He died in a way he didn't deserve.

183
00:10:35,135 --> 00:10:37,637
The time is up.

184
00:10:38,513 --> 00:10:42,809
Any Fate Reader who wants to have a go,
press your button now.

185
00:10:46,187 --> 00:10:47,188
- Oh.
- Ah…

186
00:10:47,272 --> 00:10:50,650
Twenty-nine Fate Readers
are up for the challenge.

187
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:52,318
The number went down a bit.

188
00:10:52,402 --> 00:10:54,988
- That's how hard it is.
- Of course, it is.

189
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:58,449
Here are the Fate Readers
who will present their readings.

190
00:11:00,869 --> 00:11:01,870
YOUNG MASTER PLUM BLOSSOM

191
00:11:01,953 --> 00:11:03,288
YOUNG MASTER MINT

192
00:11:03,371 --> 00:11:04,372
YOUNG MASTER BYEOLSANG

193
00:11:04,455 --> 00:11:05,456
YOUNG MASTER SEO

194
00:11:05,540 --> 00:11:08,751
- I think they're mostly shamans.
- Looks like it.

195
00:11:08,835 --> 00:11:11,796
The first to press the button
was Young Master Plum Blossom.

196
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:14,007
Please present your reading.

197
00:11:14,090 --> 00:11:17,927
When I gave my deity
the deceased's birth date and time,

198
00:11:18,011 --> 00:11:20,471
I was told he was destined
to be close to fire.

199
00:11:20,555 --> 00:11:24,142
I took that to mean
he dealt with fires as a firefighter.

200
00:11:24,225 --> 00:11:25,768
…as a firefighter.

201
00:11:28,438 --> 00:11:29,898
I'm losing my mind here.

202
00:11:30,481 --> 00:11:34,027
I was also told that he was meant
to wear heavy clothes and a heavy hat.

203
00:11:34,110 --> 00:11:37,155
…a heavy hat.

204
00:11:38,615 --> 00:11:43,286
More importantly,
I sensed a strong smell of ash.

205
00:11:43,369 --> 00:11:44,537
So did I.

206
00:11:45,455 --> 00:11:46,873
Me too.

207
00:11:46,956 --> 00:11:49,792
Based on his birth chart,
the last thing he saw

208
00:11:49,876 --> 00:11:52,295
was a raging fire

209
00:11:52,378 --> 00:11:56,966
and he probably died trapped in it.

210
00:11:59,093 --> 00:12:00,220
What on earth?

211
00:12:00,762 --> 00:12:02,055
Oh, my gosh.

212
00:12:03,723 --> 00:12:07,060
It seems
he cared deeply for others in life,

213
00:12:07,143 --> 00:12:09,145
and there was
the energy of death in his fate,

214
00:12:09,229 --> 00:12:11,689
but he fought it by saving lives.

215
00:12:11,773 --> 00:12:15,443
I think he was destined to live
as an honorable man.

216
00:12:18,613 --> 00:12:20,031
It's game over.

217
00:12:20,114 --> 00:12:22,200
Right from the start? What do we do?

218
00:12:22,283 --> 00:12:23,409
How did he do that?

219
00:12:24,661 --> 00:12:27,497
- What the heck? It's scary.
- And he's only the first one.

220
00:12:28,039 --> 00:12:30,291
Next, Young Master Mint.

221
00:12:30,917 --> 00:12:33,002
Please present your reading.

222
00:12:33,086 --> 00:12:34,420
Hmm.

223
00:12:35,129 --> 00:12:36,839
The master versus his disciple.

224
00:12:37,340 --> 00:12:39,300
SPIRITUAL MASTER, SPIRITUAL DISCIPLE

225
00:12:39,384 --> 00:12:42,512
Young Master Byeolsang is my mentor.

226
00:12:42,595 --> 00:12:44,639
I think he has the strongest aura here.

227
00:12:47,058 --> 00:12:51,104
Still, I think
I've gained some experience myself.

228
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:53,147
I want to beat him, to be honest.

229
00:12:55,817 --> 00:12:57,235
I think I'll do better.

230
00:12:57,318 --> 00:12:58,611
I just know I will.

231
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:03,157
I'll show the skills I've honed
for the last decade.

232
00:13:03,992 --> 00:13:08,830
I also get the feeling
that he was a public servant.

233
00:13:10,206 --> 00:13:12,542
"Died in the line of duty"
was what came to mind first.

234
00:13:13,710 --> 00:13:18,298
- I believe he died a noble death.
- That's right.

235
00:13:18,381 --> 00:13:21,384
What's important is,
when he died in the fire,

236
00:13:21,467 --> 00:13:23,886
something hit him hard.

237
00:13:23,970 --> 00:13:25,430
Maybe he was trapped.

238
00:13:25,513 --> 00:13:27,557
…maybe he was trapped.

239
00:13:27,640 --> 00:13:29,434
He was trapped.

240
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:33,396
It seems he suffered
a concussion or fractures.

241
00:13:33,479 --> 00:13:38,151
I think that's what killed him,
rather than the fire itself.

242
00:13:38,901 --> 00:13:41,112
I think so too. My joints hurt like crazy.

243
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:43,865
Next, Young Master Byeolsang.

244
00:13:43,948 --> 00:13:48,911
They've mentioned
that he was a public servant

245
00:13:48,995 --> 00:13:52,165
and that he fought fires and died in one.

246
00:13:52,248 --> 00:13:55,043
I got a similar reading as well.

247
00:13:55,126 --> 00:13:59,922
But it must've been an urgent situation
where he tried to escape but couldn't.

248
00:14:00,006 --> 00:14:02,300
That's what it felt like.

249
00:14:03,342 --> 00:14:05,094
He saved many lives

250
00:14:05,178 --> 00:14:08,473
but lost his own.

251
00:14:08,556 --> 00:14:11,809
He seems to have sacrificed himself.
That's what I got.

252
00:14:13,311 --> 00:14:14,979
- Wow.
- Ah…

253
00:14:15,063 --> 00:14:17,148
So many have said
that he was a firefighter.

254
00:14:19,150 --> 00:14:21,069
Next, Young Master Seo.

255
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:25,239
When I tried to sense his spirit,

256
00:14:25,323 --> 00:14:28,284
what I felt more strongly than flames
was pressure.

257
00:14:28,367 --> 00:14:30,870
I believe something fell on him,
and he was crushed to death.

258
00:14:30,953 --> 00:14:33,331
I felt that much more strongly.

259
00:14:33,414 --> 00:14:36,793
Like he was crushed and couldn't breathe.

260
00:14:36,876 --> 00:14:38,795
That was my reading.

261
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:40,505
That's the right answer, isn't it?

262
00:14:40,588 --> 00:14:43,299
Before the smoke suffocated him…

263
00:14:43,382 --> 00:14:45,426
-He'd already been crushed to death.
-Yeah.

264
00:14:45,510 --> 00:14:50,515
The moment I felt this strong sensation,
my back hurt as if it were broken.

265
00:14:50,598 --> 00:14:52,934
Gosh. So did I.

266
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:56,813
He could've been saved,
but he was stuck and couldn't move.

267
00:14:56,896 --> 00:15:00,817
He died young, before his time.

268
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:02,985
So if you ask me what killed him,

269
00:15:03,069 --> 00:15:04,779
I'd say he was crushed to death,

270
00:15:04,862 --> 00:15:07,824
rather than killed in the fire itself.

271
00:15:09,742 --> 00:15:12,662
I did feel a huge piece
of metal pressing down on me at the end.

272
00:15:12,745 --> 00:15:15,206
I should've mentioned it.
Too bad I didn't.

273
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:21,170
What do we do in this situation?

274
00:15:21,879 --> 00:15:22,964
Ah…

275
00:15:24,423 --> 00:15:25,633
This is tough.

276
00:15:27,093 --> 00:15:28,094
Fate Reapers,

277
00:15:28,177 --> 00:15:31,597
please choose the person
who read the fate most accurately.

278
00:15:31,681 --> 00:15:34,183
It's hard because so many got it right.

279
00:15:34,267 --> 00:15:37,353
The second one.
Concussion and fractures.

280
00:15:37,436 --> 00:15:40,106
But Young Master Seo was the one
who said he was crushed to death.

281
00:15:41,232 --> 00:15:43,109
I got chills
when I heard the first reading.

282
00:15:43,192 --> 00:15:45,319
- I also found him most impressive.
- I did too.

283
00:15:45,403 --> 00:15:47,155
He said he smelled ash and…

284
00:15:47,238 --> 00:15:48,364
Heavy clothes.

285
00:15:48,447 --> 00:15:50,533
I was shocked
when he got it from the start.

286
00:15:50,616 --> 00:15:51,784
Me too.

287
00:15:53,369 --> 00:15:54,453
It's a tough one.

288
00:15:56,497 --> 00:15:59,667
Let's find out
the Fate Reapers' choice.

289
00:16:01,586 --> 00:16:05,214
I thought my answer
was the most accurate,

290
00:16:05,298 --> 00:16:07,216
so I thought maybe they'd pick me.

291
00:16:07,925 --> 00:16:11,637
I said he was crushed to death,
so I think I'm the one who got it right.

292
00:16:13,097 --> 00:16:14,974
Young Master Seo
and Young Master Mint

293
00:16:15,057 --> 00:16:17,560
gave very detailed readings,

294
00:16:17,643 --> 00:16:19,770
so I was worried they might not pick me.

295
00:16:20,605 --> 00:16:21,898
The survivor is…

296
00:16:25,109 --> 00:16:26,652
Young Master Plum Blossom.

297
00:16:26,736 --> 00:16:29,280
- Oh! Congratulations.
- Thank you.

298
00:16:29,363 --> 00:16:31,449
YOUNG MASTER PLUM BLOSSOM SURVIVES

299
00:16:31,532 --> 00:16:32,700
Congratulations.

300
00:16:32,783 --> 00:16:34,118
Well done.

301
00:16:34,869 --> 00:16:36,704
His reading was very impactful.

302
00:16:36,787 --> 00:16:38,372
It really was.

303
00:16:39,207 --> 00:16:41,417
It was tough for us to decide

304
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:44,462
the survivor for this one.

305
00:16:44,545 --> 00:16:46,464
Many of you were pretty close.

306
00:16:46,547 --> 00:16:49,217
The reason we chose
Young Master Plum Blossom

307
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:51,928
was because he gave his reading first,
which is important too.

308
00:16:52,011 --> 00:16:55,139
He also mentioned
heavy equipment and the helmet,

309
00:16:55,223 --> 00:16:57,058
which was impressive.

310
00:16:57,141 --> 00:16:59,644
That's why we chose him.

311
00:17:00,603 --> 00:17:04,941
Can you tell us
exactly what you saw in the vision?

312
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:08,611
Physically, the first thing I felt
was tightness in my chest

313
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:10,154
and a bad headache.

314
00:17:10,738 --> 00:17:14,408
If he'd died of a head injury,

315
00:17:14,492 --> 00:17:15,868
I would've felt pain on the outside,

316
00:17:15,952 --> 00:17:17,620
but I felt dizzy.

317
00:17:17,703 --> 00:17:19,956
I felt suffocated, like I'd inhaled smoke.

318
00:17:20,039 --> 00:17:22,875
I saw him take off a heavy helmet.

319
00:17:22,959 --> 00:17:24,252
Hmm.

320
00:17:24,335 --> 00:17:26,629
I saw him take it off and wipe his sweat.

321
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:28,923
That's why I thought he was a firefighter.

322
00:17:29,966 --> 00:17:31,467
The second vision I saw was

323
00:17:31,551 --> 00:17:34,095
him covered in sweat
and him eating popsicles

324
00:17:34,178 --> 00:17:36,847
with his coworkers
and tapping them together.

325
00:17:36,931 --> 00:17:38,891
Oh. It's like a movie scene.

326
00:17:41,102 --> 00:17:42,103
Wow.

327
00:17:43,354 --> 00:17:44,355
Although we picked

328
00:17:44,438 --> 00:17:46,941
Young Master Plum Blossom,
we were very torn

329
00:17:47,024 --> 00:17:50,611
because Young Master Seo
also successfully figured out

330
00:17:50,695 --> 00:17:52,530
that the deceased could've been saved.

331
00:17:52,613 --> 00:17:54,574
Actually, to rescue Mr. Kim Cheolhong,

332
00:17:54,657 --> 00:17:58,244
over 250 firefighters went to the scene,

333
00:17:58,327 --> 00:18:01,289
but when they got to him,
he had already passed away.

334
00:18:01,872 --> 00:18:05,626
That part really gave me the chills.

335
00:18:05,710 --> 00:18:07,336
But you didn't pick me.

336
00:18:09,213 --> 00:18:11,424
He said, "But you didn't pick me."

337
00:18:12,008 --> 00:18:13,259
That's cute.

338
00:18:13,968 --> 00:18:15,177
He's adorable.

339
00:18:15,261 --> 00:18:16,512
Thank you, though.

340
00:18:18,097 --> 00:18:19,849
I'll try harder.

341
00:18:21,559 --> 00:18:25,187
Young Master Plum Blossom,
you may leave the hall now.

342
00:18:26,355 --> 00:18:28,733
I have a favor to ask.

343
00:18:28,816 --> 00:18:33,112
Before I leave,
can I untangle this go for the deceased?

344
00:18:33,195 --> 00:18:35,740
- Yes.
- Yes, sure.

345
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:40,494
He came prepared.

346
00:18:41,495 --> 00:18:44,498
- Maybe that's why the spirit came to him.
- Right.

347
00:18:44,582 --> 00:18:46,459
- He must be grateful.
- Hmm.

348
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:52,089
There are the Siwang,
the 10 Kings of the Underworld.

349
00:18:56,385 --> 00:18:59,722
You untie each knot in the goppae,
praying the 10 Kings show mercy

350
00:18:59,805 --> 00:19:01,641
when they judge the deceased.

351
00:19:01,724 --> 00:19:03,976
UNTYING THE KNOTS
TO HELP A SPIRIT CROSS OVER

352
00:19:04,727 --> 00:19:07,938
I was half-possessed by his spirit
when I was untying them.

353
00:19:09,482 --> 00:19:12,652
I could feel his grief
as the knots were being untied.

354
00:19:13,694 --> 00:19:17,031
I prayed that he would rest in peace
as I was untying the knots.

355
00:19:20,701 --> 00:19:22,286
May he be reborn in paradise.

356
00:19:22,370 --> 00:19:24,205
May he be reborn in paradise.

357
00:19:34,131 --> 00:19:39,387
When you untie the knots,
you can see the spirit leave.

358
00:19:40,262 --> 00:19:43,224
You neatly fold the go afterward,

359
00:19:43,307 --> 00:19:45,935
and if the ends line up perfectly,

360
00:19:46,018 --> 00:19:47,478
it means the spirit is at peace.

361
00:19:48,396 --> 00:19:49,897
Thank you. I'm done.

362
00:19:50,439 --> 00:19:51,649
That was great.

363
00:19:53,109 --> 00:19:55,444
- Congratulations.
- Good luck!

364
00:19:55,528 --> 00:19:59,532
The reason why
I really hoped to get this one

365
00:20:00,241 --> 00:20:03,369
was because I wanted
to untie the knots and send him off.

366
00:20:03,452 --> 00:20:05,079
I'm so glad I got to do that.

367
00:20:05,913 --> 00:20:09,667
Perhaps, he appreciated my intent
and helped me move forward in return.

368
00:20:11,419 --> 00:20:14,755
- Shamans have an edge in this department.
- Definitely.

369
00:20:14,839 --> 00:20:16,048
They're bound to be good.

370
00:20:16,132 --> 00:20:18,426
-They can literally see what happened.
-Yes.

371
00:20:18,509 --> 00:20:21,303
"Heavy clothes
and a heavy hat." That was it for me.

372
00:20:23,180 --> 00:20:24,598
What would be the next question?

373
00:20:26,142 --> 00:20:27,601
The next question

374
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:31,313
is the deceased's cause of death.

375
00:20:39,405 --> 00:20:40,865
LEE JAEHYEON
DIED ON AUGUST 1, 2004

376
00:20:40,948 --> 00:20:43,617
Please begin your reading now.

377
00:20:43,701 --> 00:20:47,121
Granny, Grandpa. He was born
on the 29th of the lunar February, 1977.

378
00:20:47,621 --> 00:20:51,125
Please grant me an accurate reading.

379
00:20:51,584 --> 00:20:53,461
Many of them are using flags.

380
00:20:54,670 --> 00:20:55,921
Flags.

381
00:20:56,005 --> 00:20:58,716
I see a lot of them drawing
the obanggi this time.

382
00:20:58,799 --> 00:21:00,092
Right.

383
00:21:01,927 --> 00:21:04,138
They've started drawing obanggi.

384
00:21:07,141 --> 00:21:10,644
Obanggi means flags of 5 colors.

385
00:21:10,728 --> 00:21:14,148
The most simple and common use
is to see if something's good or bad.

386
00:21:15,483 --> 00:21:18,903
Obanggi are
usually used to confirm the reading.

387
00:21:20,696 --> 00:21:22,865
Even if our deities
tell us something,

388
00:21:22,948 --> 00:21:25,993
we still have doubts sometimes
because we're only human.

389
00:21:27,995 --> 00:21:31,123
And when we do,
we check to see if the reading is right.

390
00:21:32,416 --> 00:21:34,627
Usually, white and red mean good fortune.

391
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:38,088
MEANING OF THE COLORS
WHITE, RED: POSITIVE

392
00:21:38,172 --> 00:21:40,549
Tell me the answer.

393
00:21:42,384 --> 00:21:45,513
Green implies scandal,
illness, or an accident.

394
00:21:45,596 --> 00:21:48,557
MEANING OF THE COLORS
GREEN: NEGATIVE

395
00:21:48,641 --> 00:21:50,935
HONG YULJAE
6-YEAR SHAMAN

396
00:21:54,980 --> 00:21:56,690
FAIRY PEACH BLOSSOM
6-YEAR SHAMAN

397
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:03,072
And that's how I knew
he died a tragic death.

398
00:22:04,031 --> 00:22:05,533
SEOLHWA
4-YEAR SHAMAN

399
00:22:05,616 --> 00:22:08,035
Tell me how this person passed,
Granny and Grandpa.

400
00:22:08,118 --> 00:22:10,621
Help me out here.

401
00:22:11,997 --> 00:22:14,208
I could tell
he died a tragic death.

402
00:22:15,292 --> 00:22:17,795
Oh, dear. A broken leg.

403
00:22:21,090 --> 00:22:23,050
YOUNG MASTER SEO
5-YEAR SHAMAN

404
00:22:31,851 --> 00:22:32,977
It was sudden.

405
00:22:33,644 --> 00:22:34,854
A sudden death.

406
00:22:38,107 --> 00:22:40,442
I've got my eyes on Young Master Seo.
I think he'll get it again.

407
00:22:40,526 --> 00:22:41,610
Yes.

408
00:22:42,486 --> 00:22:45,281
I watched the shamans
doing their thing,

409
00:22:45,364 --> 00:22:47,283
and honestly, I was impressed.

410
00:22:47,366 --> 00:22:49,660
Talking to the spirits
and getting everything right.

411
00:22:49,743 --> 00:22:52,788
But myungri
is an entirely different field.

412
00:22:52,872 --> 00:22:54,290
I couldn't figure it out at all.

413
00:23:03,632 --> 00:23:06,635
I used to be an IT engineer.

414
00:23:06,719 --> 00:23:09,096
But I started studying myungri

415
00:23:09,179 --> 00:23:11,473
and developed a formula
about the 24 solar terms.

416
00:23:11,557 --> 00:23:15,936
Then I created my own theory
and launched my saju business.

417
00:23:16,020 --> 00:23:17,354
My name is Pie.

418
00:23:17,980 --> 00:23:20,774
We specialize in saju and myungri.

419
00:23:20,858 --> 00:23:22,526
We can't let the shamans win.

420
00:23:22,610 --> 00:23:23,986
We have to win.

421
00:23:25,654 --> 00:23:27,990
I'm going to make it.

422
00:23:29,074 --> 00:23:30,242
I'm going to make it.

423
00:23:31,201 --> 00:23:35,122
I always make sure to analyze
one's environment and disposition.

424
00:23:35,205 --> 00:23:37,958
"What kind of path
have they taken so far and how?"

425
00:23:38,042 --> 00:23:39,710
I keep trying to gain more insight.

426
00:23:39,793 --> 00:23:43,839
PERPETUAL CALENDAR
AND BIRTH DETAILS WERE PROVIDED

427
00:23:44,423 --> 00:23:47,051
The time is up.

428
00:23:47,134 --> 00:23:51,513
Here are the Fate Readers
who will present their readings.

429
00:23:52,681 --> 00:23:54,600
Young Master Seo
got another chance.

430
00:23:54,683 --> 00:23:55,893
As expected.

431
00:23:55,976 --> 00:23:58,479
PIE
12-YEAR SAJU EXPERT

432
00:23:58,562 --> 00:23:59,605
You made it.

433
00:24:03,192 --> 00:24:04,610
SEOLHWA
4-YEAR SHAMAN

434
00:24:04,693 --> 00:24:06,070
SOHO
5-YEAR SHAMAN

435
00:24:06,153 --> 00:24:08,405
Oh, I'm in.

436
00:24:09,490 --> 00:24:12,618
The first to press the button
was Young Master Seo.

437
00:24:12,701 --> 00:24:14,745
Please present your reading.

438
00:24:15,371 --> 00:24:16,622
Young Master Seo.

439
00:24:16,705 --> 00:24:18,540
I can't wait to hear it.

440
00:24:18,624 --> 00:24:20,542
I'm curious.

441
00:24:20,626 --> 00:24:23,837
I think it was a sudden death.
That's what we call this kind of death.

442
00:24:26,340 --> 00:24:28,258
- He's right.
- That's true.

443
00:24:28,342 --> 00:24:31,720
I feel he suffered from an illness,

444
00:24:31,804 --> 00:24:34,390
and he was on a lot of medications.

445
00:24:34,473 --> 00:24:36,517
I believe he died from a disease,

446
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:39,103
something that runs in the family.

447
00:24:39,186 --> 00:24:41,855
I'm getting the image
where he feels something

448
00:24:41,939 --> 00:24:44,525
and collapses all of a sudden.

449
00:24:44,608 --> 00:24:48,237
That's how I think he passed away.

450
00:24:50,239 --> 00:24:51,865
Next up, Pie.

451
00:24:52,574 --> 00:24:54,451
In the case of Mr. Lee Jaehyeon,

452
00:24:54,535 --> 00:24:57,705
he was born in late spring
under Yang Wood,

453
00:24:57,788 --> 00:25:01,041
which symbolizes logic and learning.

454
00:25:01,125 --> 00:25:04,461
But I also see Yin Fire, which implies
artistic or intellectual talent,

455
00:25:04,545 --> 00:25:07,840
so it seems he worked out in the field.

456
00:25:07,923 --> 00:25:10,217
And if I look at his annual fortune,

457
00:25:10,300 --> 00:25:15,431
he was likely out in the field
either as a police officer or a soldier.

458
00:25:15,514 --> 00:25:19,143
I see him trying
to save others from danger.

459
00:25:21,812 --> 00:25:24,732
I noticed he was born on the month
and the day of gapjin.

460
00:25:24,815 --> 00:25:30,195
And gapjin means the azure dragon.

461
00:25:30,279 --> 00:25:32,197
It represents courage,

462
00:25:32,281 --> 00:25:34,700
bravery, and leadership.

463
00:25:34,783 --> 00:25:37,161
That's the impression I got.

464
00:25:37,244 --> 00:25:39,997
Also, Yin Fire implies

465
00:25:40,080 --> 00:25:43,333
the tendency to point out what's wrong.

466
00:25:43,417 --> 00:25:47,504
He could've been someone who saved others
from a wrong or bad situation.

467
00:25:47,588 --> 00:25:49,923
That's how I interpreted it,

468
00:25:50,007 --> 00:25:51,550
so I concluded he was

469
00:25:51,633 --> 00:25:54,303
either a police officer or a soldier.

470
00:25:54,386 --> 00:25:57,264
That's the correct answer.

471
00:25:59,641 --> 00:26:01,518
DECEASED
OCCUPATION: POLICE OFFICER

472
00:26:01,602 --> 00:26:05,314
STABBED TO DEATH
WHILE APPREHENDING A SUSPECT

473
00:26:05,397 --> 00:26:07,232
I wonder if he died in a fight

474
00:26:07,316 --> 00:26:10,527
where a knife or a gun was used.

475
00:26:11,278 --> 00:26:12,780
This is madness.

476
00:26:14,865 --> 00:26:18,535
-Saju readers are impressive too.
-Saju readers are doing amazing today.

477
00:26:19,119 --> 00:26:23,957
Saju can be more accurate
than spiritual divination, and I can win.

478
00:26:25,084 --> 00:26:26,752
Next, Seolhwa.

479
00:26:26,835 --> 00:26:30,005
- Seolhwa.
- She's the dancer-turned-shaman.

480
00:26:30,089 --> 00:26:31,882
-She cried earlier.
-Right.

481
00:26:36,512 --> 00:26:38,639
Why? Is she feeling something?

482
00:26:39,515 --> 00:26:43,185
She must be sensing
the spirit's emotions.

483
00:26:43,769 --> 00:26:46,939
I'm Seolhwa, a novice shaman
with 3 years of experience.

484
00:26:48,107 --> 00:26:50,109
We're nervous
in our own way as novices,

485
00:26:50,192 --> 00:26:52,361
and manshins are nervous in theirs.

486
00:26:52,444 --> 00:26:53,862
I'm still a novice.

487
00:26:53,946 --> 00:26:56,323
You're feeling nervous?
Then how would I feel?

488
00:26:56,406 --> 00:26:58,534
- She's an utter novice.
- What about me?

489
00:26:58,617 --> 00:27:00,702
We must do whatever we can.

490
00:27:00,786 --> 00:27:04,123
I'm still a novice,
so I'm keeping my head down.

491
00:27:04,206 --> 00:27:07,292
and I greet them with respect.

492
00:27:07,376 --> 00:27:09,586
But I'm no pushover.

493
00:27:09,670 --> 00:27:13,590
I trust my Granny and Grandpa spirits
when I read one's fortune.

494
00:27:13,674 --> 00:27:17,052
I don't see or care about anyone else
when I'm doing that.

495
00:27:18,262 --> 00:27:19,972
I don't want to bring disgrace to them.

496
00:27:23,392 --> 00:27:27,271
The first thing I saw
on this person was a bandage.

497
00:27:28,021 --> 00:27:30,732
A puncture, a stabbing with a knife.

498
00:27:30,816 --> 00:27:32,276
I see he was stabbed.

499
00:27:32,359 --> 00:27:33,402
Oh, my word.

500
00:27:35,153 --> 00:27:38,448
I also saw that his leg was broken.

501
00:27:38,532 --> 00:27:41,910
I saw a cast, and I also saw him
being taken away in an ambulance.

502
00:27:41,994 --> 00:27:44,288
Oh! This is crazy.

503
00:27:44,371 --> 00:27:46,039
He died in transit.

504
00:27:46,123 --> 00:27:50,544
It's likely he was a man in uniform
and got stabbed.

505
00:27:50,627 --> 00:27:52,546
He wore a cast and was bandaged,

506
00:27:52,629 --> 00:27:55,173
so it's likely he was hurt.

507
00:27:55,674 --> 00:27:56,758
My gosh.

508
00:27:57,426 --> 00:27:59,511
"A man in uniform was stabbed."

509
00:28:00,387 --> 00:28:01,597
That's spot-on.

510
00:28:03,265 --> 00:28:04,892
Next up, Soho.

511
00:28:06,101 --> 00:28:07,853
The person who sat next to me.

512
00:28:07,936 --> 00:28:11,440
The person in yellow, Seolhwa.

513
00:28:11,523 --> 00:28:13,066
I wanted to leave before her.

514
00:28:13,150 --> 00:28:17,029
I wanted to prove my spiritual power.

515
00:28:18,071 --> 00:28:20,407
In the vision, I sensed

516
00:28:20,490 --> 00:28:23,535
a loud smack or bang.

517
00:28:23,619 --> 00:28:25,913
I saw it was an unfortunate accident.

518
00:28:25,996 --> 00:28:29,207
I also saw him being taken
to the hospital.

519
00:28:29,291 --> 00:28:33,128
This person was a good and righteous man,

520
00:28:33,211 --> 00:28:36,340
and he would sacrifice himself
to protect others.

521
00:28:36,423 --> 00:28:38,634
In my vision,
he has something in his hand,

522
00:28:38,717 --> 00:28:41,637
and he's fighting to protect something.

523
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:44,598
Either he died in the line of duty

524
00:28:44,681 --> 00:28:47,100
or he was hurt
while trying to protect others

525
00:28:47,184 --> 00:28:49,519
and died while being taken
to the hospital.

526
00:28:52,439 --> 00:28:55,359
- Died on duty.
- Died in transit.

527
00:28:55,442 --> 00:28:57,027
-While being transported.
-Yes.

528
00:28:57,110 --> 00:28:58,987
I think this person…

529
00:29:01,823 --> 00:29:03,700
All readings have been shared.

530
00:29:04,618 --> 00:29:05,827
Fate Reapers,

531
00:29:05,911 --> 00:29:09,873
please choose the person
who read the fate most accurately.

532
00:29:09,957 --> 00:29:13,502
- Let's go with the concise, accurate one.
- Yes, of course.

533
00:29:13,585 --> 00:29:15,045
Seolhwa wasn't bad either.

534
00:29:15,128 --> 00:29:16,588
She mentioned
a uniform and stabbing.

535
00:29:16,672 --> 00:29:17,839
It was spot-on.

536
00:29:17,923 --> 00:29:20,008
But Soho actually said

537
00:29:20,092 --> 00:29:21,426
he died on his way to the hospital.

538
00:29:21,510 --> 00:29:22,552
- Did she?
- Yes.

539
00:29:22,636 --> 00:29:24,429
-That was good.
-What I liked about his reading

540
00:29:24,513 --> 00:29:27,557
was that he got the occupation
and the cause of death right.

541
00:29:27,641 --> 00:29:28,892
- Pie? You're right.
- Yes.

542
00:29:32,312 --> 00:29:35,273
To be honest, I was confident.

543
00:29:35,357 --> 00:29:37,401
I trust my deity.

544
00:29:38,860 --> 00:29:41,321
I believe in my Granny spirit.

545
00:29:43,073 --> 00:29:45,867
Please. Please pick me.

546
00:29:48,453 --> 00:29:49,496
The survivor is

547
00:29:50,288 --> 00:29:51,707
Pie.

548
00:29:55,252 --> 00:29:58,130
PIE SURVIVES

549
00:29:59,798 --> 00:30:01,299
MANSHIN KWON SUJIN
26-YEAR SHAMAN

550
00:30:01,383 --> 00:30:03,552
They're all surprised.

551
00:30:03,635 --> 00:30:06,304
A saju reader beat the shamans.

552
00:30:06,388 --> 00:30:08,432
BUSINESS SAGE KIM
8-YEAR SAJU EXPERT

553
00:30:08,515 --> 00:30:09,891
Saju.

554
00:30:10,809 --> 00:30:12,436
Saju readers have still got it.

555
00:30:14,229 --> 00:30:16,815
Pie did a lot of research

556
00:30:16,898 --> 00:30:19,735
and protected saju readers' pride.

557
00:30:19,818 --> 00:30:21,445
I'm grateful to him.

558
00:30:22,696 --> 00:30:25,157
I'm happy. So happy.

559
00:30:25,240 --> 00:30:28,326
This wasn't even my area of expertise,

560
00:30:28,410 --> 00:30:32,414
but I pulled it off,
so I felt proud and relieved.

561
00:30:34,458 --> 00:30:35,834
The late Lee Jaehyeon

562
00:30:35,917 --> 00:30:38,170
was a police officer.

563
00:30:38,253 --> 00:30:40,172
On August 1, 2004,

564
00:30:40,255 --> 00:30:42,883
while apprehending
a perpetrator on the run

565
00:30:42,966 --> 00:30:45,385
after locking up
and assaulting his girlfriend,

566
00:30:45,469 --> 00:30:48,013
he was stabbed
and killed in the line of duty.

567
00:30:48,096 --> 00:30:49,723
STABBED 9 TIMES BY SUSPECT,
DIED EN ROUTE TO THE HOSPITAL

568
00:30:49,806 --> 00:30:52,476
Oh, that's terrible.

569
00:30:55,437 --> 00:30:58,857
Again,
it was a really tough call.

570
00:30:59,483 --> 00:31:00,901
Pie was the first

571
00:31:00,984 --> 00:31:03,904
-to say he was a police officer.
-That's right.

572
00:31:03,987 --> 00:31:05,781
He also mentioned a knife

573
00:31:05,864 --> 00:31:08,867
and said he must've died
while trying to save someone else.

574
00:31:08,950 --> 00:31:10,494
That was very accurate.

575
00:31:10,577 --> 00:31:12,913
He got both the job
and the cause of death right.

576
00:31:12,996 --> 00:31:15,415
But how did you know

577
00:31:15,499 --> 00:31:17,375
it involved a fight and a knife?

578
00:31:17,459 --> 00:31:21,797
He seemed to be a brave person
and the type to rectify what's wrong.

579
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:23,548
That's why I thought

580
00:31:23,632 --> 00:31:26,468
the incident might've involved a weapon.

581
00:31:27,094 --> 00:31:30,555
-So it was his intuition.
-He interpreted it himself.

582
00:31:30,639 --> 00:31:32,516
That's part of his skill set.

583
00:31:32,599 --> 00:31:34,101
It was his intuition.

584
00:31:34,976 --> 00:31:36,436
To be honest,

585
00:31:36,520 --> 00:31:38,939
while listening to your reading,

586
00:31:39,022 --> 00:31:41,066
I thought that well-trained intuition

587
00:31:41,149 --> 00:31:45,237
is like the finger of a deity.

588
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:47,239
Well-polished knowledge
must have allowed him

589
00:31:47,322 --> 00:31:51,493
to peer into things
like the eye of a deity.

590
00:31:51,576 --> 00:31:53,245
I was very surprised.

591
00:31:54,746 --> 00:31:57,833
All that from studying… That's impressive.

592
00:31:57,916 --> 00:31:59,126
Like a deity

593
00:32:00,335 --> 00:32:01,336
pointing to the answer.

594
00:32:04,214 --> 00:32:07,217
Fate Reader Pie survived.

595
00:32:07,300 --> 00:32:09,219
- I'll see you later.
- How cool.

596
00:32:09,302 --> 00:32:10,637
That's so admirable.

597
00:32:10,720 --> 00:32:12,848
- It's cool he pulled it off with saju.
- It is.

598
00:32:12,931 --> 00:32:14,558
It's easier for shamans to do it, so…

599
00:32:14,641 --> 00:32:15,642
So impressive.

600
00:32:16,685 --> 00:32:18,895
Every time someone left,

601
00:32:18,979 --> 00:32:21,731
I thought, "I've got to move on
to the next round too."

602
00:32:21,815 --> 00:32:23,733
"Why am I still here?"

603
00:32:23,817 --> 00:32:27,487
I got jealous and antsy
each time someone survived.

604
00:32:27,571 --> 00:32:31,158
I pretended I was happy for them,
but I was actually boiling inside.

605
00:32:31,241 --> 00:32:33,243
I kept telling myself, "Get it together."

606
00:32:34,202 --> 00:32:35,203
That was awesome.

607
00:32:35,287 --> 00:32:38,915
I only mentioned uniform
and forgot to say he was a police officer.

608
00:32:38,999 --> 00:32:42,169
- You have to be even more accurate.
- I know.

609
00:32:42,252 --> 00:32:44,671
This must be why we're novices.

610
00:32:45,797 --> 00:32:47,215
- Gosh.
- This is why.

611
00:32:48,133 --> 00:32:49,426
Ah…

612
00:32:50,552 --> 00:32:52,554
I thought the shamans would beat everyone.

613
00:32:52,637 --> 00:32:54,973
- I guess you never know.
- He's a saju reader.

614
00:32:55,056 --> 00:32:57,309
- It's crazy he got the cause of death.
- I know.

615
00:32:58,143 --> 00:33:01,313
Two shamans
and one saju reader so far.

616
00:33:03,106 --> 00:33:04,941
Here is the next question.

617
00:33:14,367 --> 00:33:16,578
- What's going on?
- It's opening.

618
00:33:18,121 --> 00:33:20,123
What is this?
It's a different kind of question.

619
00:33:21,750 --> 00:33:23,251
We've got actual people now.

620
00:33:24,711 --> 00:33:26,796
- What's this?
- There are people.

621
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:27,881
What?

622
00:33:30,592 --> 00:33:32,427
Five people in hanbok.

623
00:33:34,429 --> 00:33:35,430
What's this?

624
00:33:36,223 --> 00:33:37,974
Don't tell me we should pick out a shaman.

625
00:33:39,142 --> 00:33:41,478
Looks like we need to guess who's shaman.

626
00:33:41,561 --> 00:33:44,147
Good God.

627
00:33:44,898 --> 00:33:46,191
Here is the next question.

628
00:33:46,775 --> 00:33:48,360
Who's the shaman?

629
00:33:50,111 --> 00:33:52,239
- Come on.
- This should be fun.

630
00:33:52,989 --> 00:33:54,532
Who's the shaman?

631
00:33:56,034 --> 00:33:57,911
Unbelievable.

632
00:34:00,914 --> 00:34:02,123
How funny.

633
00:34:03,416 --> 00:34:05,210
Come on, are you serious?

634
00:34:05,293 --> 00:34:08,380
Asking shamans to find a shaman?
That's harsh.

635
00:34:08,463 --> 00:34:09,923
Interesting.

636
00:34:10,006 --> 00:34:13,343
Standing before you
are 5 shamans.

637
00:34:14,678 --> 00:34:16,221
1. FLOWER HEAVENLY FAIRY

638
00:34:16,680 --> 00:34:18,431
2. SHAMAN THUNDERBOLT

639
00:34:18,890 --> 00:34:20,642
3. SHAMAN KANGSEON

640
00:34:21,142 --> 00:34:22,852
4. SAGE BEOM

641
00:34:23,311 --> 00:34:25,063
5. FAIRY WOLHWA

642
00:34:25,146 --> 00:34:27,691
However, only 2 of them

643
00:34:27,774 --> 00:34:29,150
are actual shamans

644
00:34:29,234 --> 00:34:32,362
- who have their own shrines.
- Two of them?

645
00:34:32,445 --> 00:34:34,823
The other 3 are not shamans.

646
00:34:34,906 --> 00:34:36,032
Oh, they're fakes.

647
00:34:36,116 --> 00:34:41,162
Read their fates
and find the 2 real shamans.

648
00:34:43,248 --> 00:34:45,709
Not just 1 but 2 of them?

649
00:34:45,792 --> 00:34:48,586
- This can be pretty tough.
- It's difficult.

650
00:34:48,670 --> 00:34:51,172
Wouldn't this be easier
for shamans, though?

651
00:34:51,256 --> 00:34:55,218
I'm a counselor, and I recognize
a counselor when I see one.

652
00:34:55,302 --> 00:34:56,386
Yes, you can tell.

653
00:34:57,304 --> 00:34:59,139
LEE SOBIN
20-YEAR SHAMAN

654
00:34:59,222 --> 00:35:00,724
This is so much fun.

655
00:35:00,807 --> 00:35:02,058
SEORIHWA
5-YEAR SHAMAN

656
00:35:02,142 --> 00:35:05,562
It couldn't be easier.
I can tell just by looking at their eyes.

657
00:35:06,479 --> 00:35:08,398
You can tell just by looking.

658
00:35:08,481 --> 00:35:10,358
YOUNG MASTER BYEON
15-YEAR SHAMAN

659
00:35:10,442 --> 00:35:12,235
We can tell just by looking.

660
00:35:12,319 --> 00:35:14,321
You could line up 100 people

661
00:35:14,404 --> 00:35:16,906
and tell me to find a shaman,
and I think I could.

662
00:35:16,990 --> 00:35:19,075
I've seen so many of them.

663
00:35:19,159 --> 00:35:23,997
YOUNG MASTER BYEOLSANG
11-YEAR SHAMAN

664
00:35:25,540 --> 00:35:26,791
When you do a reading
on a shaman,

665
00:35:26,875 --> 00:35:28,918
the bells often fall off the bunch.

666
00:35:32,297 --> 00:35:34,132
Two, three bells… They keep falling off.

667
00:35:42,390 --> 00:35:45,352
That's how you know they're a shaman.

668
00:35:48,146 --> 00:35:49,981
Isn't this something
only shamans can tell?

669
00:35:50,565 --> 00:35:51,858
Only shamans can tell.

670
00:35:55,028 --> 00:35:56,029
Shamans recognize

671
00:35:56,655 --> 00:35:57,947
their own kind.

672
00:35:58,031 --> 00:35:59,115
HONG YULJAE
6-YEAR SHAMAN

673
00:36:03,119 --> 00:36:05,413
Shamans have this unique gaze.

674
00:36:05,497 --> 00:36:06,498
DOEYU
7-YEAR SHAMAN

675
00:36:07,082 --> 00:36:09,834
When you look at another shaman,

676
00:36:10,377 --> 00:36:13,963
they have another pupil in their eyes
that's invisible to ordinary people.

677
00:36:14,047 --> 00:36:16,841
There's something
that looks like a deity's pupil.

678
00:36:18,843 --> 00:36:20,387
I bet most shamans can feel it.

679
00:36:33,233 --> 00:36:35,610
The shamans seem
to just keep staring, right?

680
00:36:36,611 --> 00:36:38,488
They say they can see deities.

681
00:36:39,072 --> 00:36:41,032
How can you see them?

682
00:36:43,910 --> 00:36:45,787
A Granny's face.

683
00:36:46,871 --> 00:36:49,499
LEE SOBIN
20-YEAR SHAMAN

684
00:36:50,083 --> 00:36:52,043
I was looking at numbers 1 and 3,

685
00:36:52,127 --> 00:36:55,046
and their faces turned really red,

686
00:36:55,130 --> 00:36:57,716
and I saw some elderly spirits
that looked enraged.

687
00:36:57,799 --> 00:37:00,677
As soon as I saw that, I knew it was them.

688
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:04,180
They would've had to pretend like
they were fake shamans,

689
00:37:04,264 --> 00:37:06,057
and a shaman pretending not to be one?

690
00:37:06,141 --> 00:37:07,892
No deity would be happy with that.

691
00:37:10,562 --> 00:37:12,272
We moved on
to the next question,

692
00:37:12,355 --> 00:37:14,607
and for some reason,
I didn't feel confident.

693
00:37:16,776 --> 00:37:18,319
LADY WISH
6-YEAR SHAMAN

694
00:37:24,701 --> 00:37:26,619
Help me, Granny. I can't tell.

695
00:37:26,703 --> 00:37:28,288
Is there a deity?

696
00:37:28,371 --> 00:37:29,664
My Granny spirit said,

697
00:37:29,748 --> 00:37:31,958
"Since when did you read fortunes
with your head?"

698
00:37:32,041 --> 00:37:35,462
"You're stuck because your thoughts
and greed got in the way."

699
00:37:35,545 --> 00:37:39,340
So I decided to trust what I saw and felt,

700
00:37:39,424 --> 00:37:41,301
and that's
when I could see things clearly.

701
00:37:44,721 --> 00:37:47,599
I could see deities
in only numbers 1 and 3,

702
00:37:47,682 --> 00:37:50,852
and the rest had closed doors
and looked dark,

703
00:37:50,935 --> 00:37:52,687
so I knew they weren't with any deities.

704
00:37:54,647 --> 00:37:58,234
Does she serve deities
in her own shrine?

705
00:37:58,318 --> 00:37:59,652
Her name is Shaman Kangseon.

706
00:37:59,736 --> 00:38:02,697
I ask you to tell me
if she serves deities.

707
00:38:02,781 --> 00:38:04,616
Young Master Dragon.

708
00:38:04,699 --> 00:38:07,535
He used to be an actor.
The handsome guy.

709
00:38:07,619 --> 00:38:10,538
I was an actor for about 16 years

710
00:38:10,622 --> 00:38:12,165
before I became a shaman.

711
00:38:12,248 --> 00:38:14,793
I'm a novice
with less than 6 months of experience,

712
00:38:14,876 --> 00:38:16,336
the talented Young Master Dragon.

713
00:38:16,419 --> 00:38:20,215
My deities said
although I never made it big as an actor,

714
00:38:21,216 --> 00:38:22,801
they'd make sure

715
00:38:23,384 --> 00:38:25,595
I make a name for myself as a shaman.

716
00:38:25,678 --> 00:38:27,847
They often tell me this when I pray.

717
00:38:27,931 --> 00:38:30,475
Because I've only just become a shaman,

718
00:38:30,558 --> 00:38:33,853
I thought I'd feel things more powerfully.

719
00:38:34,521 --> 00:38:37,774
That lady's pretending.

720
00:38:39,442 --> 00:38:40,819
I was confident.

721
00:38:42,153 --> 00:38:45,156
The saju readers have a shot
because they have all their birth details.

722
00:38:45,240 --> 00:38:47,242
- They have the birth charts.
- Right.

723
00:38:48,159 --> 00:38:50,578
You know, shamans are born
with a certain birth chart.

724
00:38:50,662 --> 00:38:54,541
Shamans, celebrities, and people
with such occupations have similar saju.

725
00:38:54,624 --> 00:38:55,792
Oh.

726
00:38:55,875 --> 00:38:57,460
I think saju readers
will do better.

727
00:38:58,711 --> 00:39:00,296
FATE-TELLER
9-YEAR SAJU EXPERT

728
00:39:00,380 --> 00:39:02,799
META MYUNGRI JOON
15-YEAR SAJU EXPERT

729
00:39:06,094 --> 00:39:09,889
Shamans' sajus share
something in common.

730
00:39:09,973 --> 00:39:13,643
Excessive Wood and Water energy.

731
00:39:13,726 --> 00:39:17,856
Water is the divine energy,
and Wood is the human energy.

732
00:39:18,731 --> 00:39:22,902
Water enriches wood.
Water gives life to trees.

733
00:39:22,986 --> 00:39:26,656
Receiving messages from deities
and delivering them to the world.

734
00:39:26,739 --> 00:39:30,326
That's the disposition
shamans are born with.

735
00:39:32,453 --> 00:39:35,498
Number 4's not it. He's a good actor.

736
00:39:36,541 --> 00:39:38,835
There's one among numbers 1, 3, and 5.

737
00:39:38,918 --> 00:39:40,712
FLOWER HEAVENLY FAIRY,
SHAMAN KANGSEON, FAIRY WOLHWA

738
00:39:41,546 --> 00:39:43,798
The time is up.

739
00:39:44,340 --> 00:39:46,885
Any Fate Reader who wants to give it a go,

740
00:39:46,968 --> 00:39:48,595
press your button now.

741
00:39:50,805 --> 00:39:53,182
- See?
- Everyone wants to do it.

742
00:39:53,266 --> 00:39:54,475
That was quick.

743
00:39:56,227 --> 00:40:00,023
Forty-one Fate Readers are up
for the challenge.

744
00:40:00,523 --> 00:40:03,151
- Oh, good. Lots of new people.
- Yes.

745
00:40:03,234 --> 00:40:08,323
Lady Wish,
please present your reading.

746
00:40:08,907 --> 00:40:10,867
She used to be an archer.

747
00:40:10,950 --> 00:40:12,911
A third-generation shaman.

748
00:40:12,994 --> 00:40:18,082
I was torn
among numbers 1, 3, and 5.

749
00:40:18,166 --> 00:40:21,252
As for number 1, I saw a Grandpa spirit.

750
00:40:21,336 --> 00:40:23,963
A deity who has the ability to cure.

751
00:40:24,047 --> 00:40:27,550
I think that's the guardian deity
that she serves.

752
00:40:28,176 --> 00:40:30,053
A Grandpa spirit?

753
00:40:30,136 --> 00:40:34,390
For number 3,
Shaman Kangseon, I see a young lady.

754
00:40:34,474 --> 00:40:38,561
She also has the saju of a shaman.

755
00:40:39,270 --> 00:40:41,689
Yes, spot-on.

756
00:40:41,773 --> 00:40:43,775
