for a long time.

1006
00:54:00,529 --> 00:54:03,365
"You can tell this much from one's saju?"

1007
00:54:03,449 --> 00:54:05,701
I'm eager to make people think that.

1008
00:54:07,119 --> 00:54:10,789
I will say number 2 is the guy
who won the lottery.

1009
00:54:10,873 --> 00:54:12,040
Let me explain why.

1010
00:54:12,541 --> 00:54:17,045
In saju, there are 3 "storages"
that symbolize wealth.

1011
00:54:17,129 --> 00:54:19,673
This man's saju is breaking them.

1012
00:54:19,757 --> 00:54:23,051
By "breaking," I mean
that the storages are open.

1013
00:54:23,135 --> 00:54:26,096
When one's storages are open,
they hit a jackpot.

1014
00:54:26,180 --> 00:54:28,265
That's why I say

1015
00:54:28,348 --> 00:54:32,603
he strongly attracts wealth and romance.

1016
00:54:32,686 --> 00:54:35,272
Romance too?

1017
00:54:35,355 --> 00:54:39,318
Now, Mr. Lee Jaeseok
was born with Wood in his saju,

1018
00:54:39,401 --> 00:54:41,278
but there's a lot of Metal
in his saju too.

1019
00:54:41,361 --> 00:54:45,741
I can take that to mean
he's under a tremendous amount of stress.

1020
00:54:45,824 --> 00:54:50,329
My answer is number 1's the lightning,
and number 2's the windfall.

1021
00:54:50,412 --> 00:54:51,830
LIGHTNING, WINDFALL

1022
00:54:51,914 --> 00:54:55,250
The 2 saju readers
gave the exact same answer.

1023
00:54:55,334 --> 00:54:56,627
Fascinating.

1024
00:54:56,710 --> 00:54:58,754
Next, Rumi.

1025
00:54:58,837 --> 00:55:00,839
Please present your reading.

1026
00:55:01,590 --> 00:55:03,175
- Spiritual tarot.
- Yes.

1027
00:55:03,258 --> 00:55:05,177
A lot of baseball players' wives
go to see her.

1028
00:55:05,260 --> 00:55:06,970
Oh, that's her.

1029
00:55:07,054 --> 00:55:10,933
First of all,
I think Mr. Lee Jaeseok's the windfall

1030
00:55:11,016 --> 00:55:15,312
and Mr. Kim Seongoh was hit by lightning.

1031
00:55:15,854 --> 00:55:20,275
The reason is, the cards I got
were the Wheel of Fortune,

1032
00:55:20,943 --> 00:55:25,572
the Magician, and King of Pentacles.

1033
00:55:26,240 --> 00:55:29,535
"He's proud he survived it."

1034
00:55:29,618 --> 00:55:31,828
That's how I interpreted it.

1035
00:55:32,454 --> 00:55:33,705
Ah…

1036
00:55:34,206 --> 00:55:35,207
Goodness.

1037
00:55:35,874 --> 00:55:39,378
If he were hit
by lightning and survived,

1038
00:55:39,461 --> 00:55:41,171
that's as good

1039
00:55:41,255 --> 00:55:43,924
as having won the lottery.

1040
00:55:45,676 --> 00:55:47,135
That's a great interpretation.

1041
00:55:48,011 --> 00:55:50,180
It all comes down to how you interpret it.

1042
00:55:51,056 --> 00:55:53,100
Next, Beentarot.

1043
00:55:53,725 --> 00:55:55,894
- Please present your reading.
- It's his first presentation.

1044
00:55:55,978 --> 00:55:58,897
- Yoon Gai's younger brother.
- Actress Yoon Gai's brother.

1045
00:55:58,981 --> 00:56:03,068
Honestly, winning the lottery and getting
hit by lightning are both very unlikely.

1046
00:56:03,151 --> 00:56:07,656
The cards for number 1
were the Ace of Pentacles and the Tower.

1047
00:56:07,739 --> 00:56:11,451
You can see money and lightning.
Very straightforward.

1048
00:56:11,535 --> 00:56:15,664
Number 4 got the Judgement card

1049
00:56:15,747 --> 00:56:19,084
and the Ace of Swords piercing through it.

1050
00:56:20,252 --> 00:56:22,838
So I say number 4 was hit by lightning,

1051
00:56:22,921 --> 00:56:24,590
and number 1 scored a windfall

1052
00:56:24,673 --> 00:56:26,466
by winning the lottery.

1053
00:56:27,009 --> 00:56:28,844
Our answers are the same.

1054
00:56:29,428 --> 00:56:32,848
Tarot is so fascinating too.
How did they get the same answer?

1055
00:56:32,931 --> 00:56:34,725
TAROT MASTERS
NUMBER 4

1056
00:56:35,183 --> 00:56:37,185
Next, Young Master Jiseon.

1057
00:56:41,148 --> 00:56:43,525
I knew even before they came in.

1058
00:56:43,609 --> 00:56:44,818
YOUNG MASTER JISEON
13-YEAR SHAMAN

1059
00:56:45,277 --> 00:56:47,112
My Granny spirit stood behind me and said,

1060
00:56:48,113 --> 00:56:49,114
"It's him."

1061
00:56:50,532 --> 00:56:54,494
So I thought,
"It's you. This mission's for me."

1062
00:56:55,996 --> 00:56:58,457
Based on my reading,

1063
00:56:58,540 --> 00:57:00,667
number 2 won the lottery

1064
00:57:00,751 --> 00:57:03,712
and number 4 was hit by lightning.

1065
00:57:07,633 --> 00:57:09,676
As for number 2,

1066
00:57:09,760 --> 00:57:12,054
simply put, there were nobles

1067
00:57:12,137 --> 00:57:15,098
among his ancestors,
people of high status.

1068
00:57:15,182 --> 00:57:17,184
I see a few of those lords with him.

1069
00:57:17,267 --> 00:57:22,189
People in his family
used to hold high offices,

1070
00:57:22,272 --> 00:57:25,609
which means they accumulated good karma.

1071
00:57:25,692 --> 00:57:28,570
So, their descendants
are able to reap the benefits

1072
00:57:28,654 --> 00:57:30,697
in terms of wealth.

1073
00:57:30,781 --> 00:57:32,199
As for number 4,

1074
00:57:32,282 --> 00:57:34,493
he's had a rough life.

1075
00:57:34,576 --> 00:57:37,704
Simply put,
nothing comes together for him.

1076
00:57:37,788 --> 00:57:40,832
That's why I say he was hit by lightning.

1077
00:57:41,625 --> 00:57:43,502
Oh!

1078
00:57:43,585 --> 00:57:46,755
SHAMAN
NUMBER 4

1079
00:57:47,297 --> 00:57:49,508
All readings have been shared.

1080
00:57:51,551 --> 00:57:52,552
The survivor is…

1081
00:57:59,685 --> 00:58:01,603
Young Master Jiseon.

1082
00:58:03,647 --> 00:58:05,607
YOUNG MASTER JISEON SURVIVES

1083
00:58:05,691 --> 00:58:07,693
The kid's crying.

1084
00:58:07,776 --> 00:58:09,653
No, don't cry.

1085
00:58:09,736 --> 00:58:12,322
- Oh, no.
- Oh, dear baby.

1086
00:58:12,406 --> 00:58:14,282
- He's the youngest, 18-year-old.
- Ow, geez.

1087
00:58:14,366 --> 00:58:15,575
Ow, geez.

1088
00:58:16,743 --> 00:58:17,911
Oh, what do we do?

1089
00:58:18,662 --> 00:58:21,415
- Oh, my word.
- Geez.

1090
00:58:22,708 --> 00:58:24,626
Gosh.

1091
00:58:24,710 --> 00:58:26,753
Why are you crying?

1092
00:58:27,504 --> 00:58:28,505
Young Master Jiseon.

1093
00:58:28,588 --> 00:58:31,049
- No, I just got a little emotional.
- You got emotional?

1094
00:58:31,842 --> 00:58:35,470
I think my mom and dad
will be delighted.

1095
00:58:35,554 --> 00:58:39,141
I talked to them in my head.
"I made it."

1096
00:58:40,684 --> 00:58:42,352
I'll brag to them later.

1097
00:58:42,436 --> 00:58:45,105
They've always been my biggest supporters.

1098
00:58:46,440 --> 00:58:49,484
I didn't get to see them
before coming here. So I will later.

1099
00:58:50,485 --> 00:58:51,570
I'm so thankful.

1100
00:58:53,905 --> 00:58:55,574
- Would you like some tissue?
- Yes.

1101
00:58:56,491 --> 00:58:57,743
I tried not to cry.

1102
00:58:58,910 --> 00:59:00,954
It's embarrassing
to cry around celebrities.

1103
00:59:04,791 --> 00:59:07,461
- He was so accurate.
- He's so good.

1104
00:59:07,544 --> 00:59:11,047
-He got it in one go.
-Seriously. It's truly incredible.

1105
00:59:11,131 --> 00:59:13,467
- He actually got it right.
- I know.

1106
00:59:14,301 --> 00:59:20,807
Mr. Lee Beomjun won the 467th
lottery draw on November 12, 2011.

1107
00:59:20,891 --> 00:59:22,309
Wow!

1108
00:59:22,392 --> 00:59:28,231
He received a windfall
of 1.435 billion won.

1109
00:59:28,315 --> 00:59:29,858
Gosh, I'm so jealous.

1110
00:59:30,484 --> 00:59:33,278
I wish I got a windfall like that.

1111
00:59:33,862 --> 00:59:37,073
On May 19, 2008,

1112
00:59:37,157 --> 00:59:39,034
Mr. Kim Seongoh was struck by lightning

1113
00:59:39,117 --> 00:59:40,702
-while riding his motorcycle
-No way.

1114
00:59:40,786 --> 00:59:43,413
-and miraculously woke up after 9 days.
-Oh, my days.

1115
00:59:43,497 --> 00:59:47,375
- It was literally a bolt of lightning.
- That's impressive.

1116
00:59:49,503 --> 00:59:51,379
Thank goodness!

1117
00:59:51,463 --> 00:59:52,756
What a relief.

1118
00:59:54,132 --> 00:59:57,677
Mr. Lee Beomjun,
the lottery winner.

1119
00:59:57,761 --> 01:00:02,974
Lottery winners often say they had a dream
about fire or poop the night before.

1120
01:00:03,058 --> 01:00:06,394
- Or a pig.
- Or ancestors giving them the numbers.

1121
01:00:06,478 --> 01:00:09,105
Mr. Lee, what about you?
Did you have any dreams?

1122
01:00:09,564 --> 01:00:10,565
Yes.

1123
01:00:10,649 --> 01:00:15,529
In my dream, I was walking down
the street, and a stranger showed up

1124
01:00:15,612 --> 01:00:19,783
-and stabbed me in the neck like this.
-Oh, gosh.

1125
01:00:19,866 --> 01:00:21,785
But when he did,

1126
01:00:21,868 --> 01:00:24,538
someone other than me
started bleeding from the neck.

1127
01:00:24,621 --> 01:00:29,334
The blood gushed out like a waterfall.

1128
01:00:29,835 --> 01:00:31,294
That's a good dream.

1129
01:00:31,378 --> 01:00:32,629
That's a great dream.

1130
01:00:33,129 --> 01:00:34,214
He saw blood.

1131
01:00:35,048 --> 01:00:37,217
I was at my ripe age of late 20s,

1132
01:00:37,300 --> 01:00:39,553
but I was so scared
when I woke up from the dream,

1133
01:00:39,636 --> 01:00:40,887
so I went to sleep next to my mom.

1134
01:00:40,971 --> 01:00:42,764
That's how real the dream felt.

1135
01:00:42,848 --> 01:00:45,058
I guess that dream was a sign.

1136
01:00:47,018 --> 01:00:49,145
-That's right.
-Oh, how interesting.

1137
01:00:50,313 --> 01:00:53,108
Mr. Kim Seongoh,
what happened to you

1138
01:00:53,191 --> 01:00:56,486
might be even rarer
than winning the lottery.

1139
01:00:56,570 --> 01:00:59,531
It's rare enough to get struck
by lightning, but you even survived.

1140
01:00:59,614 --> 01:01:03,493
It was drizzling, and I saw
lightning strike a spot ahead of me.

1141
01:01:03,577 --> 01:01:06,705
But I was in a hurry,
so I took my motorcycle,

1142
01:01:06,788 --> 01:01:10,500
and got struck by lightning
at the top of a mountain pass.

1143
01:01:10,584 --> 01:01:14,462
I fell off a cliff with my motorcycle.

1144
01:01:14,546 --> 01:01:16,506
- My gosh.
- Oh, dear.

1145
01:01:16,590 --> 01:01:17,924
Oh, my days.

1146
01:01:18,008 --> 01:01:20,719
But like a miracle,

1147
01:01:20,802 --> 01:01:23,471
I woke up after 9 days.

1148
01:01:23,555 --> 01:01:25,765
That's incredible.

1149
01:01:25,849 --> 01:01:29,436
Gosh, that's such a relief.

1150
01:01:30,604 --> 01:01:32,647
I was a professional golfer.

1151
01:01:32,731 --> 01:01:34,733
Wow.

1152
01:01:34,816 --> 01:01:39,237
But I couldn't play the sport
anymore after the accident,

1153
01:01:39,321 --> 01:01:42,741
and now I'm a trot singer.

1154
01:01:43,700 --> 01:01:45,452
What?

1155
01:01:45,535 --> 01:01:47,412
My goodness.

1156
01:01:51,583 --> 01:01:55,128
His life took a 180.

1157
01:01:55,211 --> 01:01:58,465
I thought
they'd never get it right.

1158
01:01:58,548 --> 01:02:01,301
I didn't think anyone would get it.

1159
01:02:01,384 --> 01:02:04,471
I'm grateful that Young Master Jiseon did.
Thank you.

1160
01:02:04,554 --> 01:02:06,514
I got goosebumps all over.

1161
01:02:06,598 --> 01:02:10,310
Young Master Jiseon.
Mr. Kim Seongoh got struck by lightning.

1162
01:02:10,393 --> 01:02:12,187
Will he be successful?

1163
01:02:18,860 --> 01:02:20,779
Well, let's see.

1164
01:02:20,862 --> 01:02:23,448
When people sing trot songs,
some sing for fun,

1165
01:02:23,531 --> 01:02:27,118
but some do it
because of han.

1166
01:02:27,202 --> 01:02:30,080
Mr. Kim sings with his heart and han.

1167
01:02:30,747 --> 01:02:34,376
Next year, around April and May,
he will definitely…

1168
01:02:39,506 --> 01:02:43,760
reach a high before he goes down.

1169
01:02:45,512 --> 01:02:47,055
He goes down?

1170
01:02:47,138 --> 01:02:49,182
- He'll go down?
- He goes down?

1171
01:02:49,265 --> 01:02:51,101
He'll still have his moment.

1172
01:02:51,184 --> 01:02:52,936
That's what counts.

1173
01:02:53,019 --> 01:02:54,229
That's right.

1174
01:02:54,938 --> 01:02:56,272
Swoosh.

1175
01:02:57,565 --> 01:03:00,443
For identifying
the windfall and lightning,

1176
01:03:00,527 --> 01:03:02,904
Young Master Jiseon survived.

1177
01:03:02,988 --> 01:03:04,781
- Wow.
- Good for him.

1178
01:03:06,366 --> 01:03:08,660
If you were faced
with 4 strangers

1179
01:03:08,743 --> 01:03:11,788
and had to guess who won the lottery,
would you be able to do it?

1180
01:03:11,871 --> 01:03:12,956
It'd be difficult, right?

1181
01:03:13,039 --> 01:03:16,167
But I, the youngest, pulled it off.

1182
01:03:18,420 --> 01:03:19,796
He started when he was 5.

1183
01:03:19,879 --> 01:03:22,340
I know.
He's the youngest shaman here.

1184
01:03:22,424 --> 01:03:24,676
A fun fact about him is that
his guardian spirit is a Granny spirit,

1185
01:03:24,759 --> 01:03:28,763
- so he wears a woman's hanbok.
- Young Master Jiseon?

1186
01:03:28,847 --> 01:03:30,348
That's why he's so elegant.

1187
01:03:31,307 --> 01:03:33,518
- How graceful.
- Thank you.

1188
01:03:33,601 --> 01:03:35,061
Congratulations.

1189
01:03:35,145 --> 01:03:37,564
- Congratulations.
- The youngest pulled it off.

1190
01:03:37,647 --> 01:03:39,232
- Yes.
- Bluetooth handshake.

1191
01:03:40,233 --> 01:03:41,568
"Bluetooth."

1192
01:03:42,861 --> 01:03:45,155
His mic pack's dangling
from his back.

1193
01:03:47,615 --> 01:03:49,284
Here is the next mission.

1194
01:03:51,202 --> 01:03:54,998
This is the fate for you to read.

1195
01:03:59,002 --> 01:04:00,003
- Mmm?
- Huh?

1196
01:04:03,506 --> 01:04:04,716
What's that?

1197
01:04:04,799 --> 01:04:06,634
- What the heck?
- Huh, what?

1198
01:04:06,718 --> 01:04:08,053
What a strange sight.

1199
01:04:08,136 --> 01:04:09,387
That's gross.

1200
01:04:09,471 --> 01:04:11,139
- This is insane.
- What is this?

1201
01:04:11,222 --> 01:04:12,891
What even is that?

1202
01:04:12,974 --> 01:04:14,309
What am I looking at?

1203
01:04:14,392 --> 01:04:16,227
-What the…
-What is this?

1204
01:04:16,311 --> 01:04:18,313
What the… What am I to do?

1205
01:04:18,396 --> 01:04:20,190
What's going on?

1206
01:04:20,273 --> 01:04:21,566
Oh, geez…

1207
01:04:22,108 --> 01:04:23,359
I can't believe this.

1208
01:04:23,943 --> 01:04:25,070
What are we to guess?

1209
01:04:25,612 --> 01:04:27,947
The next fate
for you to read is…

1210
01:05:24,295 --> 01:05:26,297
Translated by Jennifer Jean Lim
